==English==
===Etymology===
* From Spanish ''Filipinas''; from Spanish ''Felipe'', the name of a King of Spain

===Pronunciation===
* fi-li-peeh'-no
* peeh-li-peeh'-noh

===Proper noun===
'''Filipino'''

# One of two national languages of the [[Philippines]], the other being English. Filipino is based on [[Tagalog]].

====Synonyms====
*(''language'') [[Pilipino]]<!--Wikipedia makes it seem like not quiet a synonym-->

===Proper noun===
'''Filipino''' {{m}}/{{f}}/{{n}}, '''[[Filipina]]''' {{f}} (''plural:'' '''[[Filipinos]]''' {{m}}/{{f}}/{{n}}, '''[[Filipinas]]''' {{f}})

# [[nationality|Nationality]] of residents or citizens of the [[Philippines]].
# [[ethnicity|Ethnicity]] of people identified with the Philippines, its culture{{,}} and heritage.

====Synonyms====
*(''ethnicity'') [[Flip]], [[Noypi]], [[Pinoy]], [[Pinay]]

===Adjective===
'''Filipino'''

# Of or pertaining to the [[Philippines]] or its [[people]].
# Of or pertaining to Filipino, the language of the [[Philippines]].

====Synonyms====
*(''of the Philippines or its people'') [[Philippine]]

